The paper discusses a class of attacks on Intelligent Transportation Systems (ITS) that exploit wireless communication vulnerabilities. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Security (cs.CR) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also uses Markov Decision Process and Approximate Policy Iteration algorithms to derive potent attack policies, indicating that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the attack policies and compares them to other policies, suggesting that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
